## 15) Setup API Sync Endpoint for Mobile App
- **Status:** Not Started
- **Priority:** HIGH
- **Description:** Create REST API endpoints for mobile app to sync pharmacy data:
  - GET /api/pharmacies - Fetch all pharmacies with timestamps
  - GET /api/pharmacies/:id - Single pharmacy data
  - Support incremental sync (fetch changes since last sync timestamp)
  - Add caching headers for performance
  - Implement data pagination
  - Add search/filter capabilities (by name, city, emergency status)
  - Version API endpoints (v1)
- **Files to Create:**
  - backend/routes/api/v1/pharmacies.js
  - backend/services/syncService.js
  - backend/middleware/caching.js
- **Acceptance Criteria:**
  - GET /api/v1/pharmacies returns all pharmacies as JSON
  - Supports query params: ?limit=50&offset=0
  - Supports filtering: ?emergency=true&city=Tunis
  - Timestamps included for sync tracking
  - Caching headers set (max-age, ETag)
  - Supports gzip compression
- **Estimate:** 2-3 hours

